DEPTH_BUFFER_BIT.comment: Clearing buffers: Passed to clear to clear the current depth buffer.

STENCIL_BUFFER_BIT.comment: Clearing buffers: Passed to clear to clear the current stencil buffer.

COLOR_BUFFER_BIT.comment: Clearing buffers: Passed to clear to clear the current color buffer.

POINTS.comment: Rendering primitives: Passed to drawElements or drawArrays to draw single points.

LINES.comment: Rendering primitives: Passed to drawElements or drawArrays to draw lines. Each vertex connects to the one after it.

LINE_LOOP.comment: Rendering primitives: Passed to drawElements or drawArrays to draw lines. Each set of two vertices is treated as a separate line segment.

LINE_STRIP.comment: Rendering primitives: Passed to drawElements or drawArrays to draw a connected group of line segments from the first vertex to the last.

TRIANGLES.comment: Rendering primitives: Passed to drawElements or drawArrays to draw triangles. Each set of three vertices creates a separate triangle.

TRIANGLE_STRIP.comment: Rendering primitives: Passed to drawElements or drawArrays to draw a connected group of triangles.

TRIANGLE_FAN.comment: Rendering primitives: Passed to drawElements or drawArrays to draw a connected group of triangles. Each vertex connects to the previous and the first vertex in the fan.

ZERO.comment: Blending modes: Passed to blendFunc or blendFuncSeparate to turn off a component.

ONE.comment: Blending modes: Passed to blendFunc or blendFuncSeparate to turn on a component.

SRC_COLOR.comment: Blending modes: Passed to blendFunc or blendFuncSeparate to multiply a component by the source elements color.

ONE_MINUS_SRC_COLOR.comment: Blending modes: Passed to blendFunc or blendFuncSeparate to multiply a component by one minus the source elements color.

SRC_ALPHA.comment: Blending modes: Passed to blendFunc or blendFuncSeparate to multiply a component by the source's alpha.

ONE_MINUS_SRC_ALPHA.comment: Blending modes: Passed to blendFunc or blendFuncSeparate to multiply a component by one minus the source's alpha.

DST_ALPHA.comment: Blending modes: Passed to blendFunc or blendFuncSeparate to multiply a component by the destination's alpha.

ONE_MINUS_DST_ALPHA.comment: Blending modes: Passed to blendFunc or blendFuncSeparate to multiply a component by one minus the destination's alpha.

DST_COLOR.comment: Blending modes: Passed to blendFunc or blendFuncSeparate to multiply a component by the destination's color.

ONE_MINUS_DST_COLOR.comment: Blending modes: Passed to blendFunc or blendFuncSeparate to multiply a component by one minus the destination's color.

SRC_ALPHA_SATURATE.comment: Blending modes: Passed to blendFunc or blendFuncSeparate to multiply a component by the minimum of source's alpha or one minus the destination's alpha.

CONSTANT_COLOR.comment: Blending modes: Passed to blendFunc or blendFuncSeparate to specify a constant color blend function.

ONE_MINUS_CONSTANT_COLOR.comment: Blending modes: Passed to blendFunc or blendFuncSeparate to specify one minus a constant color blend function.

CONSTANT_ALPHA.comment: Blending modes: Passed to blendFunc or blendFuncSeparate to specify a constant alpha blend function.

ONE_MINUS_CONSTANT_ALPHA.comment: Blending modes: Passed to blendFunc or blendFuncSeparate to specify one minus a constant alpha blend function.

FUNC_ADD.comment: Blending equations: Passed to blendEquation or blendEquationSeparate to set an addition blend function.

FUNC_SUBTRACT.comment: Blending equations: Passed to blendEquation or blendEquationSeparate to specify a subtraction blend function (source - destination).

FUNC_REVERSE_SUBTRACT.comment: Blending equations: Passed to blendEquation or blendEquationSeparate to specify a reverse subtraction blend function (destination - source).

BLEND_EQUATION.comment: Getting GL parameter information: Passed to getParameter to get the current RGB blend function.

BLEND_EQUATION_RGB.comment: Getting GL parameter information: Passed to getParameter to get the current RGB blend function. Same as BLEND_EQUATION

BLEND_EQUATION_ALPHA.comment: Getting GL parameter information: Passed to getParameter to get the current alpha blend function. Same as BLEND_EQUATION

BLEND_DST_RGB.comment: Getting GL parameter information: Passed to getParameter to get the current destination RGB blend function.

BLEND_SRC_RGB.comment: Getting GL parameter information: Passed to getParameter to get the current destination RGB blend function.

BLEND_DST_ALPHA.comment: Getting GL parameter information: Passed to getParameter to get the current destination alpha blend function.

BLEND_SRC_ALPHA.comment: Getting GL parameter information: Passed to getParameter to get the current source alpha blend function.

BLEND_COLOR.comment: Getting GL parameter information: Passed to getParameter to return a the current blend color.

ARRAY_BUFFER_BINDING.comment: Getting GL parameter information: Passed to getParameter to get the array buffer binding.

ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER_BINDING.comment: Getting GL parameter information: Passed to getParameter to get the current element array buffer.

LINE_WIDTH.comment: Getting GL parameter information: Passed to getParameter to get the current lineWidth (set by the lineWidth method).

ALIASED_POINT_SIZE_RANGE.comment: Getting GL parameter information: Passed to getParameter to get the current size of a point drawn with GL_POINTS

ALIASED_LINE_WIDTH_RANGE.comment: Getting GL parameter information: Passed to getParameter to get the range of available widths for a line. Returns a length-2 array with the lo value at 0, and hight at 1.

CULL_FACE_MODE.comment: Getting GL parameter information: Passed to getParameter to get the current value of cullFace. Should return FRONT, BACK, or FRONT_AND_BACK

FRONT_FACE.comment: Getting GL parameter information: Passed to getParameter to determine the current value of frontFace. Should return CW or CCW.

DEPTH_RANGE.comment: Getting GL parameter information: Passed to getParameter to return a length-2 array of floats giving the current depth range.

DEPTH_WRITEMASK.comment: Getting GL parameter information: Passed to getParameter to determine if the depth write mask is enabled.

DEPTH_CLEAR_VALUE.comment: Getting GL parameter information: Passed to getParameter to determine the current depth clear value.

DEPTH_FUNC.comment: Getting GL parameter information: Passed to getParameter to get the current depth function. Returns NEVER, ALWAYS, LESS, EQUAL, LEQUAL, GREATER, GEQUAL, or NOTEQUAL.

STENCIL_CLEAR_VALUE.comment: Getting GL parameter information: Passed to getParameter to get the value the stencil will be cleared to.

STENCIL_FUNC.comment: Getting GL parameter information: Passed to getParameter to get the current stencil function. Returns NEVER, ALWAYS, LESS, EQUAL, LEQUAL, GREATER, GEQUAL, or NOTEQUAL.

STENCIL_FAIL.comment: Getting GL parameter information: Passed to getParameter to get the current stencil fail function. Should return KEEP, REPLACE, INCR, DECR, INVERT, INCR_WRAP, or DECR_WRAP.

STENCIL_PASS_DEPTH_FAIL.comment: Getting GL parameter information: Passed to getParameter to get the current stencil fail function should the depth buffer test fail. Should return KEEP, REPLACE, INCR, DECR, INVERT, INCR_WRAP, or DECR_WRAP.

STENCIL_PASS_DEPTH_PASS.comment: Getting GL parameter information: Passed to getParameter to get the current stencil fail function should the depth buffer test pass. Should return KEEP, REPLACE, INCR, DECR, INVERT, INCR_WRAP, or DECR_WRAP.

STENCIL_REF.comment: Getting GL parameter information: Passed to getParameter to get the reference value used for stencil tests.

STENCIL_VALUE_MASK.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

STENCIL_WRITEMASK.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

STENCIL_BACK_FUNC.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

STENCIL_BACK_FAIL.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

STENCIL_BACK_PASS_DEPTH_FAIL.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

STENCIL_BACK_PASS_DEPTH_PASS.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

STENCIL_BACK_REF.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

STENCIL_BACK_VALUE_MASK.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

STENCIL_BACK_WRITEMASK.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

VIEWPORT.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter, returns an Int32Array with four elements for the current viewport dimensions.

SCISSOR_BOX.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter, returns an Int32Array with four elements for the current scissor box dimensions.

COLOR_CLEAR_VALUE.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

COLOR_WRITEMASK.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

UNPACK_ALIGNMENT.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

PACK_ALIGNMENT.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

MAX_TEXTURE_SIZE.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

MAX_VIEWPORT_DIMS.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

SUBPIXEL_BITS.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

RED_BITS.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

GREEN_BITS.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

BLUE_BITS.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

ALPHA_BITS.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

DEPTH_BITS.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

STENCIL_BITS.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

POLYGON_OFFSET_UNITS.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

POLYGON_OFFSET_FACTOR.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

TEXTURE_BINDING_2D.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

SAMPLE_BUFFERS.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

SAMPLES.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

SAMPLE_COVERAGE_VALUE.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

SAMPLE_COVERAGE_INVERT.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

COMPRESSED_TEXTURE_FORMATS.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

VENDOR.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

RENDERER.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

VERSION.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

IMPLEMENTATION_COLOR_READ_TYPE.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

IMPLEMENTATION_COLOR_READ_FORMAT.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

BROWSER_DEFAULT_WEBGL.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

STATIC_DRAW.comment: Buffers: Passed to bufferData as a hint about whether the contents of the buffer are likely to be used often and not change often.

STREAM_DRAW.comment: Buffers: Passed to bufferData as a hint about whether the contents of the buffer are likely to not be used often.

DYNAMIC_DRAW.comment: Buffers: Passed to bufferData as a hint about whether the contents of the buffer are likely to be used often and change often.

ARRAY_BUFFER.comment: Buffers: Passed to bindBuffer or bufferData to specify the type of buffer being used.

ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER.comment: Buffers: Passed to bindBuffer or bufferData to specify the type of buffer being used.

BUFFER_SIZE.comment: Buffers: Passed to getBufferParameter to get a buffer's size.

BUFFER_USAGE.comment: Buffers: Passed to getBufferParameter to get the hint for the buffer passed in when it was created.

CURRENT_VERTEX_ATTRIB.comment: Vertex attributes: Passed to getVertexAttrib to read back the current vertex attribute.

CULL_FACE.comment: Culling: Passed to enable/disable to turn on/off culling. Can also be used with getParameter to find the current culling method.

FRONT.comment: Culling: Passed to cullFace to specify that only front faces should be culled.

BACK.comment: Culling: Passed to cullFace to specify that only back faces should be culled.

FRONT_AND_BACK.comment: Culling: Passed to cullFace to specify that front and back faces should be culled.

BLEND.comment: Enabling and disabling: Passed to enable/disable to turn on/off blending. Can also be used with getParameter to find the current blending method.

DEPTH_TEST.comment: Enabling and disabling: Passed to enable/disable to turn on/off the depth test. Can also be used with getParameter to query the depth test.

DITHER.comment: Enabling and disabling: Passed to enable/disable to turn on/off dithering. Can also be used with getParameter to find the current dithering method.

POLYGON_OFFSET_FILL.comment: Enabling and disabling: Passed to enable/disable to turn on/off the polygon offset. Useful for rendering hidden-line images, decals, and or solids with highlighted edges. Can also be used with getParameter to query the scissor test.

SAMPLE_ALPHA_TO_COVERAGE.comment: Enabling and disabling: Passed to enable/disable to turn on/off the alpha to coverage. Used in multi-sampling alpha channels.

SAMPLE_COVERAGE.comment: Enabling and disabling: Passed to enable/disable to turn on/off the sample coverage. Used in multi-sampling.

SCISSOR_TEST.comment: Enabling and disabling: Passed to enable/disable to turn on/off the scissor test. Can also be used with getParameter to query the scissor test.

STENCIL_TEST.comment: Enabling and disabling: Passed to enable/disable to turn on/off the stencil test. Can also be used with getParameter to query the stencil test.

CW.comment: Front face directions: Passed to frontFace to specify the front face of a polygon is drawn in the clockwise direction

CCW.comment: Front face directions: Passed to frontFace to specify the front face of a polygon is drawn in the counter clockwise direction

DONT_CARE.comment: Hints: There is no preference for this behavior.

FASTEST.comment: Hints: The most efficient behavior should be used.

NICEST.comment: Hints: The most correct or the highest quality option should be used.

GENERATE_MIPMAP_HINT.comment: Hints: Hint for the quality of filtering when generating mipmap images with WebGLRenderingContext.generateMipmap().

FRAGMENT_SHADER.comment: Shaders: Passed to createShader to define a fragment shader.

VERTEX_SHADER.comment: Shaders: Passed to createShader to define a vertex shader

COMPILE_STATUS.comment: Shaders: Passed to getShaderParamter to get the status of the compilation. Returns false if the shader was not compiled. You can then query getShaderInfoLog to find the exact error

DELETE_STATUS.comment: Shaders: Passed to getShaderParamter to determine if a shader was deleted via deleteShader. Returns true if it was, false otherwise.

LINK_STATUS.comment: Shaders: Passed to getProgramParameter after calling linkProgram to determine if a program was linked correctly. Returns false if there were errors. Use getProgramInfoLog to find the exact error.

VALIDATE_STATUS.comment: Shaders: Passed to getProgramParameter after calling validateProgram to determine if it is valid. Returns false if errors were found.

ATTACHED_SHADERS.comment: Shaders: Passed to getProgramParameter after calling attachShader to determine if the shader was attached correctly. Returns false if errors occurred.

ACTIVE_ATTRIBUTES.comment: Shaders: Passed to getProgramParameter to get the number of attributes active in a program.

ACTIVE_UNIFORMS.comment: Shaders: Passed to getProgramParamter to get the number of uniforms active in a program.

MAX_VERTEX_ATTRIBS.comment: Shaders: The maximum number of entries possible in the vertex attribute list.

MAX_TEXTURE_IMAGE_UNITS.comment: Shaders: Implementation dependent number of maximum texture units. At least 8.

NEVER.comment: Depth or stencil tests: Passed to depthFunction or stencilFunction to specify depth or stencil tests will never pass. i.e. Nothing will be drawn.

LESS.comment: Depth or stencil tests: Passed to depthFunction or stencilFunction to specify depth or stencil tests will pass if the new depth value is less than the stored value.

EQUAL.comment: Depth or stencil tests: Passed to depthFunction or stencilFunction to specify depth or stencil tests will pass if the new depth value is equals to the stored value.

LEQUAL.comment: Depth or stencil tests: Passed to depthFunction or stencilFunction to specify depth or stencil tests will pass if the new depth value is less than or equal to the stored value.

GREATER.comment: Depth or stencil tests: Passed to depthFunction or stencilFunction to specify depth or stencil tests will pass if the new depth value is greater than the stored value.

NOTEQUAL.comment: Depth or stencil tests: Passed to depthFunction or stencilFunction to specify depth or stencil tests will pass if the new depth value is not equal to the stored value.

GEQUAL.comment: Depth or stencil tests: Passed to depthFunction or stencilFunction to specify depth or stencil tests will pass if the new depth value is greater than or equal to the stored value.

ALWAYS.comment: Depth or stencil tests: Passed to depthFunction or stencilFunction to specify depth or stencil tests will always pass. i.e. Pixels will be drawn in the order they are drawn.

ACTIVE_TEXTURE.comment: Textures: The current active texture unit.

READ_BUFFER.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

UNPACK_ROW_LENGTH.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

UNPACK_SKIP_ROWS.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

UNPACK_SKIP_PIXELS.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

PACK_ROW_LENGTH.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

PACK_SKIP_ROWS.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

PACK_SKIP_PIXELS.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

TEXTURE_BINDING_3D.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

UNPACK_SKIP_IMAGES.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

UNPACK_IMAGE_HEIGHT.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

MAX_3D_TEXTURE_SIZE.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

MAX_ELEMENTS_VERTICES.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

MAX_ELEMENTS_INDICES.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

MAX_TEXTURE_LOD_BIAS.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

MAX_FRAGMENT_UNIFORM_COMPONENTS.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

MAX_VERTEX_UNIFORM_COMPONENTS.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

MAX_ARRAY_TEXTURE_LAYERS.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

MIN_PROGRAM_TEXEL_OFFSET.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

MAX_PROGRAM_TEXEL_OFFSET.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

MAX_VARYING_COMPONENTS.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

FRAGMENT_SHADER_DERIVATIVE_HINT.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

RASTERIZER_DISCARD.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

VERTEX_ARRAY_BINDING.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

MAX_VERTEX_OUTPUT_COMPONENTS.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

MAX_FRAGMENT_INPUT_COMPONENTS.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

MAX_SERVER_WAIT_TIMEOUT.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

MAX_ELEMENT_INDEX.comment: Getting GL parameter information: passed to getParameter

VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_DIVISOR_ANGLE.comment: ANGLE_instanced_arrays: Describes the frequency divisor used for instanced rendering.

UNMASKED_VENDOR_WEBGL.comment: WEBGL_debug_renderer_info: Passed to getParameter to get the vendor string of the graphics driver.

UNMASKED_RENDERER_WEBGL.comment: WEBGL_debug_renderer_info: Passed to getParameter to get the renderer string of the graphics driver.

MAX_TEXTURE_MAX_ANISOTROPY_EXT.comment: EXT_texture_filter_anisotropic: Returns the maximum available anisotropy.

TEXTURE_MAX_ANISOTROPY_EXT.comment: EXT_texture_filter_anisotropic: Passed to texParameter to set the desired maximum anisotropy for a texture.

COMPRESSED_RGB_S3TC_DXT1_EXT.comment: WEBGL_compressed_texture_s3tc: A DXT1-compressed image in an RGB image format.

COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT1_EXT.comment: WEBGL_compressed_texture_s3tc: A DXT1-compressed image in an RGB image format with a simple on/off alpha value.

COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT3_EXT.comment: WEBGL_compressed_texture_s3tc: A DXT3-compressed image in an RGBA image format. Compared to a 32-bit RGBA texture, it offers 4:1 compression.

COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT5_EXT.comment: WEBGL_compressed_texture_s3tc: A DXT5-compressed image in an RGBA image format. It also provides a 4:1 compression, but differs to the DXT3 compression in how the alpha compression is done.

COMPRESSED_RG11_EAC.comment: WEBGL_compressed_texture_etc: Two-channel (red and green) unsigned format compression.

COMPRESSED_SIGNED_RG11_EAC.comment: WEBGL_compressed_texture_etc: Two-channel (red and green) signed format compression.

COMPRESSED_RGB8_ETC2.comment: WEBGL_compressed_texture_etc: Compresses RBG8 data with no alpha channel.

COMPRESSED_RGBA8_ETC2_EAC.comment: WEBGL_compressed_texture_etc: Compresses RGBA8 data. The RGB part is encoded the same as RGB_ETC2, but the alpha part is encoded separately.

COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ETC2.comment: WEBGL_compressed_texture_etc: Compresses sRBG8 data with no alpha channel.

COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ETC2_EAC.comment: WEBGL_compressed_texture_etc: Compresses sRGBA8 data. The sRGB part is encoded the same as SRGB_ETC2, but the alpha part is encoded separately.

COMPRESSED_RGB8_PUNCHTHROUGH_ALPHA1_ETC2.comment: WEBGL_compressed_texture_etc: Similar to RGB8_ETC, but with ability to punch through the alpha channel, which means to make it completely opaque or transparent.

COMPRESSED_SRGB8_PUNCHTHROUGH_ALPHA1_ETC.comment: WEBGL_compressed_texture_etc: Similar to SRGB8_ETC, but with ability to punch through the alpha channel, which means to make it completely opaque or transparent.

COMPRESSED_RGB_PVRTC_4BPPV1_IMG.comment: WEBGL_compressed_texture_pvrtc: RGB compression in 4-bit mode. One block for each 44 pixels.

COMPRESSED_RGBA_PVRTC_4BPPV1_IMG.comment: WEBGL_compressed_texture_pvrtc: RGBA compression in 4-bit mode. One block for each 44 pixels.

COMPRESSED_RGB_PVRTC_2BPPV1_IMG.comment: WEBGL_compressed_texture_pvrtc: RGB compression in 2-bit mode. One block for each 84 pixels.

COMPRESSED_RGBA_PVRTC_2BPPV1_IMG.comment: WEBGL_compressed_texture_pvrtc: RGBA compression in 2-bit mode. One block for each 84 pixe

COMPRESSED_RGB_ETC1_WEBGL.comment: WEBGL_compressed_texture_etc1: Compresses 24-bit RGB data with no alpha channel.

COMPRESSED_RGB_ATC_WEBGL.comment: WEBGL_compressed_texture_atc: Compresses RGB textures with no alpha channel.

COMPRESSED_RGBA_ATC_EXPLICIT_ALPHA_WEBGL.comment: WEBGL_compressed_texture_atc: Compresses RGBA textures using explicit alpha encoding (useful when alpha transitions are sharp).

COMPRESSED_RGBA_ATC_INTERPOLATED_ALPHA_W.comment: WEBGL_compressed_texture_atc: Compresses RGBA textures using interpolated alpha encoding (useful when alpha transitions are gradient).

UNSIGNED_INT_24_8_WEBGL.comment: WEBGL_depth_texture: Unsigned integer type for 24-bit depth texture data.

MIN_EXT.comment: EXT_blend_minmax: Produces the minimum color components of the source and destination colors.

MAX_EXT.comment: EXT_blend_minmax: Produces the maximum color components of the source and destination colors.

SRGB_EXT.comment: EXT_sRGB: Unsized sRGB format that leaves the precision up to the driver.

SRGB_ALPHA_EXT.comment: EXT_sRGB: Unsized sRGB format with unsized alpha component.

SRGB8_ALPHA8_EXT.comment: EXT_sRGB: Sized (8-bit) sRGB and alpha formats.

FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_COLOR_ENCODING_EX.comment: EXT_sRGB: Returns the framebuffer color encoding.

FRAGMENT_SHADER_DERIVATIVE_HINT_OES.comment: OES_standard_derivatives: Indicates the accuracy of the derivative calculation for the GLSL built-in functions: dFdx, dFdy, and fwidth.

MAX_COLOR_ATTACHMENTS_WEBGL.comment: WEBGL_draw_buffers: Maximum number of framebuffer color attachment points

MAX_DRAW_BUFFERS_WEBGL.comment: WEBGL_draw_buffers: Maximum number of draw buffers

VERTEX_ARRAY_BINDING_OES.comment: OES_vertex_array_object: The bound vertex array object (VAO).

QUERY_COUNTER_BITS_EXT.comment: EXT_disjoint_timer_query: The number of bits used to hold the query result for the given target.

QUERY_RESULT_AVAILABLE_EXT.comment: EXT_disjoint_timer_query: A Boolean indicating whether or not a query result is available.

GPU_DISJOINT_EXT.comment: EXT_disjoint_timer_query: A Boolean indicating whether or not the GPU performed any disjoint operation.
